Ask HN: 2023 Year of Linux on Phones?
text:
Now that we're done with the year of linux on servers, desktop and laptops, is it (should be) about time it really comes to our phones?

Postmarketos, pine64 are great examples of projects driving the community (and tech) forward.

What do you think?

In my opinion it feels it needs some money to be poured in, maybe a "big player" coming in with a "phone we can fix", and hack.
